<a name="3483"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Get More Press with CES Unveiled</div>
<br />

<IMG hspace=5 align=right src="/images/content/CES_Unveiled-Converted(2).gif" width=305 height=60>There are many reasons to sign up today for one or both of the 2010 International CES Unveiled events. They include ABC, CBS, CNBC, CNET, Consumer Reports, ESPN, Financial Times, Fox, The New York Times, and Wall Street Journal. More than 400 media from the Northeast have already registered for the CES NY Press Preview featuring <A href="mailto:Unveiled@NY">Unveiled@NY</A> and CES Unveiled in Las Vegas. Will they be talking about you?<BR><BR>&nbsp;<A href="mailto:Unveiled@NY">Unveiled@NY</A> on November 10, offers an invaluable opportunity to promote your products in time for the holiday sales cycle. Unveiled in Vegas on January 5, gives you the undivided attention of the press two days before CES begins.<BR><BR>A simple tabletop set-up makes it easy for your team to network with the top industry and consumer media, build relationships and generate coverage. <BR>Exhibitors receive: 
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text>Exposure to hundreds of influential, credentialed media and analysts. </LI>
<LI class=text>Extensive pre-event promotion to CES' worldwide media list via e-mail, news wires, print materials, direct individual pitching and Web promotion. </LI>
<LI class=text>Contact lists of pre-registered and confirmed media/analysts. </LI>
<LI class=text>150-word product description and photo in the Unveiled program guide within Consumer Electronics Vision magazine, which is distributed at the press events, to CE Vision's 23,000 industry readers and to thousands more on-site at the International CES. </LI>
<LI class=text>Your product displayed among Innovations 2010 Design and Engineering Awards Honorees' products – a must-see for press and analysts.</LI></UL>Sign up today to take advantage of all the pre-event promotional opportunities. <BR><BR>Contact: <A href="mailto:CESUnveiled@CE.org">CESUnveiled@CE.org</A>. Visit <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/cesunveiled">CESweb.org/CESUnveiled</A> for more information.
