<br />

<IMG height=159 hspace=5 src="/images/content/USCSlogo.jpg" width=150 align=right>December 10, 2009 <BR>2 p.m. EST<BR><BR>Do you want to learn practical tips about intellectual property law and exporting your products to foreign markets?&nbsp; As a CES exhibitor, you are encouraged to participate in a free webinar hosted by the U.S. Commercial Service International Buyer Program and the Global Information and Communications Technologies Team.<BR><BR>Presented by Dr. Lothar Determann, Partner with Baker and McKenzie LLC, and an expert in international technology law, this webinar will provide you with valuable information on this subject to ensure your company is protected. Dr. Determann will inform you of the laws to consider when selling to foreign buyers in the United States and abroad; highlight business models and some legal considerations for international distribution; as well as discuss the pitfalls and risks associated with contract localization. In addition, learn about the various government resources available on intellectual property rights.<BR><BR><A href="https://emenuapps.ita.doc.gov/ePublic/newWebinarRegistration.jsp?SmartCode=0Q2F" target=_blank>Register now for this webinar</A> and learn more about the various services offered by the Commercial Service at the show, including export counseling and one-on-one meetings with trade specialists from around the world. 
